The Commissioner of Police FCT, CP Bala Ciroma, has ordered an investigation into the suspected abduction of 17-year-old Gift Abiikor. He is a student of Federal Government College Rubochi, Abuja. DSP Anjuguri Manzah, Police Public Relations Officer, in a statement, said Gift was abducted by unknown persons in the early hours of Tuesday. It said: “According to one Ahmed Adamu, who reported the incident to the police, some armed men stormed his house at about 0100hrs and abducted Gift Abiikor while asleep the same bed with his children. “The unfortunate incident happened at the residence of Ahmed Adamu, which is outside the premises of Federal Government College Rubochi.” The command assured that it is making a concerted effort to rescue the victim and unravel the circumstances behind his abduction. Last Friday, the Police arrested the Chief of Ushafa, Alhaji Mohammed Baba, and his secretary, Danlami Busa, over the murder of ASP Eric Isaiah. 